\/DC\" ","\/\/                                 ^","\/\/            \"AC\/DC\" should be a single component!"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When these situations occur, we need to encode (or â€œescapeâ€) the slash in our path component,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"so it wonâ€™t be confused with the path delimiters. URLs use a form of encoding called ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"percent-encoding"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"because it encodes binary data using ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"%XX\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" strings, where ","type":"text"},{"code":"XX","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a hexadecimal byte value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For the ASCII forward-slash character, the byte value is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"2F"},{"type":"text","text":", so the URL shown above would become:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["\"https:\/\/example.com\/music\/bands\/AC%2FDC\"","\/\/                                 ^^^ ðŸ˜Œ"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Percent-encoding is particularly important when building strings for URL components at runtime, because it means that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"even "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"\/\""},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"?\""},{"type":"text","text":" characters in user input wonâ€™t be confused with path delimiters or other characters with special"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"meaning to the URL. Additionally, since percent-encoding always produces an ASCII string, we can use it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to encode Unicode text in URLs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["func urlForProfile(_ username: String) -> WebURL {","  var url  = WebURL(\"https:\/\/example.com\/\")!